Most Important Pattern
Almost ALL digit problems use this template:
while n > 0:
    digit = n % 10
    # process digit
    n = n // 10


Some other Important

1. Check Neon Number
Neon Number : Sum of digits of square = original number
Example: 9
9^2=81
8+1=9

2. Check Automorphic Number
Automorphic Number : Number whose square ends with same number.
Example:25
25^2=625
Ends with 25.

3. Harshad (Niven) Number : A number divisible by sum of its digits.
Example : 18
1+8=9
18÷9=2

